{"section": "A9.74", "question": "When a unit is elimiated by KIA on the IFT table, is the SW destroyed?", "expected_answer": "Make a dr on the same column of the IFT for each SW/Gun possessed by the eliminated units. A -1 DRM applies to the SW Destruction dr if the KIA ws due to a fully-tracked AFV OVR. If the Final dr is a KIA, that SW/Gun is eliminated; if it's a K, that SW/Gun is malfunctioned.", "assistant_response": "When a unit is eliminated by a KIA result on the IFT (Infantry Fire Table), the SW (Support Weapon) it possesses may be destroyed through Random SW/Gun Destruction. After a Final KIA result occurs, a die roll is made on the same column of the IFT for each SW/Gun possessed by the eliminated unit. If the Final die roll also results in a KIA, then that SW/Gun is eliminated. If the roll results in a K, the SW/Gun is malfunctioned, or eliminated if it was already malfunctioned or had an \"X#\" contact【4:1†source】.", "judgment": "correct", "comments": ""}
