{"section": "A4.42", "question": "A squad carrying 5 portage points has how many Movement Factors?", "expected_answer": "2", "assistant_response": "A squad carrying portage points in excess of its Inherent Portage Capacity (IPC) will have its Movement Factor (MF) reduced. Each squad has an Inherent Portage Capacity (IPC) of 3 Portage Points (PP). If a squad carries more than 3 PP, it loses 1 MF for each PP carried in excess of its IPC. Therefore, a squad carrying 5 PP would have its MF reduced by 2, since it is carrying 2 PP over its IPC.\n\nThe basic MF for a squad is 4. By carrying 5 PP, the squad would lose 2 MF, resulting in a total of 2 MF for that movement phase【4:6†source】.", "judgment": "correct", "comments": ""}
{"section": "A7.36", "question": "A 5-4-8 squad has Assault Fire and is pinned. It is attacking in the APh. What is its FP?", "expected_answer": "3", "assistant_response": "A 5-4-8 squad with Assault Fire that is pinned while attacking in the Advancing Fire Phase (AFPh) will have its firepower (FP) modifications as follows:\n\n1. The basic FP is halved because it is the AFPh, where all firepower is generally halved【4:18†source】.\n2. Being pinned further halves the FP【4:2†source】.\n3. The squad has Assault Fire, which allows it to add 1 FP after all other modifications and rounding up any fractions【4:0†source】【4:4†source】.\n\nCalculating the FP:\n- Start with an inherent FP of 5.\n- Halve this for the AFPh: \\(5 / 2 = 2.5\\).\n- Halve it again due to being pinned: \\(2.5 / 2 = 1.25\\).\n- Apply Assault Fire bonus: \\(1.25 + 1 = 2.25\\), which rounds up to 3 using Fractional Rounding Up (FRU)【4:0†source】.\n\nTherefore, the final FP of the pinned 5-4-8 squad with Assault Fire in the AFPh is 3.", "judgment": "correct", "comments": ""}
